a delete button on a computer.

00:36.402 --> 00:37.770
[quietly] Wow.

00:37.802 --> 00:40.772
<i>[electronic music]</i>

00:40.805 --> 00:47.746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:50.582 --> 00:52.751
Have you ever looked
at a photograph of yourself

00:52.784 --> 00:55.454
and thought,
"That's what I look like?

00:55.487 --> 00:56.655
Ugh."

00:56.689 --> 00:58.691
We often think we look bad

00:58.723 --> 01:01.093
or not right in photos

01:01.127 --> 01:04.495
because photos show us
what we really look like

01:04.530 --> 01:06.231
to other people.

01:06.265 --> 01:08.733
The you that
you're used to seeing

01:08.766 --> 01:11.269
is mirror you.

01:11.302 --> 01:14.774
Every mirror you look into
reverses your face.

01:14.807 --> 01:17.176
Most selfie cameras do this too,

01:17.209 --> 01:20.612
so we tend to prefer
that version of ourselves.

01:20.646 --> 01:22.647
If you wanna see yourself
in a mirror

01:22.680 --> 01:24.783
the way other people see you
in real life,

01:24.816 --> 01:26.318
take two mirrors

01:26.352 --> 01:28.820
and position them
at a 90-degree angle.

01:28.853 --> 01:32.191
What you see won't be
yourself reversed,

01:32.224 --> 01:34.427
but how you look in real life.

01:34.459 --> 01:36.628
<i>So who would you say
you are really?</i>

01:36.662 --> 01:38.698
<i>Are you how you look?</i>

01:38.730 --> 01:39.798
<i>Or how you dress?</i>

01:40.081 --> 01:42.951
<i>Or are you the atoms
that make you up?</i>

01:43.734 --> 01:46.805
Because all of those things
change throughout your life.

01:46.838 --> 01:48.607
Ah, maybe
the real common thread,

01:48.639 --> 01:50.409
that which doesn't change,

01:50.442 --> 01:52.110
is your history,

01:52.142 --> 01:53.544
your memory.

01:53.577 --> 01:56.180
<i>But what if we remember things
differently</i>

01:56.213 --> 01:58.749
from the way
they actually happened.

01:58.832 --> 02:02.670
Does that mean
we don't know ourselves?

02:05.772 --> 02:07.441
False memories are

02:07.475 --> 02:10.378
frighteningly easy to create.

02:10.412 --> 02:11.862
Today, we're gonna make some,

02:11.880 --> 02:13.610
