that other people

06:45.886 --> 06:47.822
truly understand their own...

06:50.657 --> 06:53.294
An interesting manifestation
of this bias

06:53.328 --> 06:54.429
is something called...

06:56.496 --> 06:58.400
It is surprisingly easy

06:58.433 --> 07:00.669
to fool someone into believing

07:00.701 --> 07:03.304
they made a choice
that they never did,

07:03.337 --> 07:04.873
and the amazing thing is that

07:04.905 --> 07:07.975
they'll also defend
that fake choice

07:08.008 --> 07:10.845
as if it were
what they had always wanted.

07:10.878 --> 07:12.429
[film reel humming]

07:12.463 --> 07:14.599
<i>We feel like
we know ourselves pretty well.</i>

07:14.631 --> 07:16.768
<i>We know why
we like the things we like.</i>

07:16.899 --> 07:19.504
<i>We know why we decided
to do the things that we did.</i>

07:19.937 --> 07:21.205
<i>But do we?</i>

07:21.239 --> 07:24.810
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:24.843 --> 07:28.847
